The paper deals with nonrigid image registration, which is a common problem in computer vision and image processing. The use of kernel regression and joint saliency maps suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The focus on local structures and deformations also suggests that the paper may be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Finally, the use of block matching and iterative regression suggests that the paper may also be relevant to graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
